Wilczkowo  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Lubomino, within Lidzbark County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It is located on Highway 593 about halfway between Dobre Miasto on the east and Mi≈Çakowo on the west. The village is located in the historical region of Warmia, which was part of the Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth until the Partitions of Poland in the late 18th century.
